"title": "5312: feasting",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5312",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Taking part in festive meals that were often a feature of Israel's celebrations of religious festivals.</p>\n<h2>Feasting on special occasions</h2>\n<h3>To mark a covenant</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen31:54\">GEN 31:54</a></strong> <em>The sacrifice and the meal were important elements in the covenant-making process.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen26:28-Gen26:31\">GEN 26:28–26:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod24:11\">EXO 24:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor11:25-1Cor11:26\">1CO 11:25–11:26</a></p>\n<h3>Weddings</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg14:10\">JDG 14:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen29:22\">GEN 29:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth2:18\">EST 2:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt22:2\">MAT 22:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John2:1-John2:10\">JHN 2:1–2:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev19:9\">REV 19:9</a></p>\n<h3>Family celebrations</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen21:8\">GEN 21:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke15:23-Luke15:24\">LUK 15:23–15:24</a></p>\n<h3>National celebrations</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs1:25\">1KI 1:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth9:17\">EST 9:17</a></p>\n<h2>Israel's religious feasts</h2>\n<h3>Passover (or the Feast of Unleavened Bread) to celebrate the exodus</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod23:15\">EXO 23:15</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut16:1-Deut16:3\">DEU 16:1–16:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev23:4-Lev23:6\">LEV 23:4–23:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr35:17\">2CH 35:17</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:17\">MAT 26:17</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:41\">LUK 2:41</a></p>\n<h3>Pentecost, to celebrate the early harvest</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:22\">EXO 34:22</a></strong> <em>Pentecost was also known in the OT as “the Feast of Weeks” or the “Feast of Harvest”.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod23:16\">EXO 23:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num28:26\">NUM 28:26</a></p>\n<h3>The Feast of Tabernacles, to celebrate the autumn harvest</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod23:16\">EXO 23:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev23:34\">LEV 23:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut16:13\">DEU 16:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra3:4\">EZR 3:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh8:14\">NEH 8:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech14:16\">ZEC 14:16</a></p>\n<h3>The Feast of Dedication, to celebrate the rededication of the temple</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:22\">JHN 10:22</a></strong></p>\n<h3>The Feast of Purim, to celebrate deliverance</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth9:17\">EST 9:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth9:22\">EST 9:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth9:26\">EST 9:26</a></p>\n<h2>Feasting amongst God's people</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh8:10\">NEH 8:10</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:46\">ACT 2:46</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs3:15\">1KI 3:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth8:17\">EST 8:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth9:17\">EST 9:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job1:4\">JOB 1:4</a></p>\n<h2>Feasting amongst the heathen</h2>\n<h3>Examples of pagan feasts</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam30:16\">1SA 30:16</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan5:1\">DAN 5:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:21-Mark6:28\">MRK 6:21–6:28</a></p>\n<h3>Warnings and instructions to Christians regarding pagan feasts</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor10:27-1Cor10:28\">1CO 10:27–10:28</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet4:3-1Pet4:4\">1PE 4:3–4:4</a></p>\n<h2>Feasting as an occasion to sin</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor10:7\">1CO 10:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod32:6\">EXO 32:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam25:36\">1SA 25:36</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam13:28\">2SA 13:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hab2:15\">HAB 2:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor10:28\">1CO 10:28</a></p>\n<h2>Feasting as an evangelistic occasion</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:29\">LUK 5:29</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark2:16-Mark2:17\">MRK 2:16–2:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke15:2\">LUK 15:2</a></p>\n<h2>Feasting defended by Jesus Christ</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt11:19\">MAT 11:19</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:34-Luke7:35\">LUK 7:34–7:35</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:14-Matt9:15\">MAT 9:14–9:15</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark2:18-Mark2:20\">MRK 2:18–2:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:33-Luke5:35\">LUK 5:33–5:35</a></p>\n<h2>Feasting as a symbol of spiritual blessings</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt22:2\">MAT 22:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov9:1-Prov9:6\">PRO 9:1–9:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa25:6\">ISA 25:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa55:1-Isa55:2\">ISA 55:1–55:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke14:15\">LUK 14:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev3:20\">REV 3:20</a></p>\n<h2>Feasting in heaven</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev19:9\">REV 19:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:11\">MAT 8:11</a></p>",
